Section 0: AZ-900 Course

---

- What is the certification about?
	- Tests foundational knowledge of cloud services and how those serives are provided with Microsoft Azure

- Three main concepts:
	- Describe cloud concepts
	- Describe Azure architecture and services
	- Describe Azure management and governance

- All virtual machines are required to be part of a private network
	-> Virtual - simulating a real thing in the cloud

- Some notes on virtual machines:
	- Can automate virtual machine launching via scripts
		-> Don't need to go through web UI
	- Can connect to the virtual machine remotely
	- Charges stop when you stop the service
	- Easier to upgrade the size of the machine that it is to create a new one
		-> Size - number of processors, ram, etc...
		-> All installed software remains

- AZ-900 is a lifetime exam

